nd, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1244–after 1340":"1244–after 1340","1240–1301":"1240–1301","1242–Male":"1242–Deceased","1244–1340":"1244–1340","1257–1340":"1257–1340","1290–Female":"1290–Deceased","1212–1273":"1212–1273","1220–1271":"1220–1271","liv. abt. 1337":"about 1337","abt 1290":"about 1290","abt. 1336":"about 1336","ABT 1268":"about 1268","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1340":"1340","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1271":"1271","1290":"1290","ABT 1273":"about 1273","1257":"1257","1301":"1301","1212":"1212","1244":"1244","after 1340":"after 1340","about 1340":"about 1340","of Bishopsbourne, Kent, Eng":"Bishopsbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Hougham nr. Dover, Kent, Eng.":"Hougham, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Bishopsbourne, Kent, Eng":"Bishopsbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom","of Hougham nr. Dover, Kent, Eng.":"Hougham, Kent, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Hougham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Kent): habitational name from Hougham (Kent), or, less often, from Hougham (Lincolnshire). The Kent placename may derive from an Old English personal name <i>Huhha</i> or Old English <i>hōh</i> ‘heel, spur of land’ + <i>hām</i> ‘village, homestead’, while the Lincolnshire placename probably takes its name from Hough on the Hill (a nearby place called with Old English <i>haga</i> ‘hedge, enclosure’) + Old English <i>hām</i> ‘village, homestead’ or <i>hamm</i> ‘water meadow’."],"variants":[{"name":"Hufham","meanings":["Probably an altered form of English   Hougham  ."]}]},{"name":"Beatrice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["and French form of   Beatrix  , which was quite popular in England during the Middle Ages, and strongly revived in the 19th century. It is most famous as the name of Dante's beloved, and is borne by the elder (  b. 1988 ) of the Duke of York's daughters."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Beatrice de Hougham was born in 1244, in Bishopsbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom, her father, Robert de Hougham, was 33 and her mother, Beatrice, was 25. She married John de Bourne about 1336, in Hougham, Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died after 1340, and was buried in Bishopsbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1244–after 1340":"1244–pärast 1340","1240–1301":"1240–1301","1242–Male":"1242–Surnud","1244–1340":"1244–1340","1257–1340":"1257–1340","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1212–1273":"1212–1273","1220–1271":"1220–1271","liv. abt. 1337":"umbes 1337","abt 1290":"umbes 1290","abt. 1336":"umbes 1336","ABT 1268":"umbes 1268","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1340":"1340","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1271":"1271","1290":"1290","ABT 1273":"umbes 1273","1257":"1257","1301":"1301","1212":"1212","1244":"1244","after 1340":"pärast 1340","about 1340":"umbes 1340","of Bishopsbourne, Kent, Eng":"Bishopsbourne, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hougham nr. Dover, Kent, Eng.":"Hougham, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bishopsbourne, Kent, Eng":"Bishopsbourne, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Hougham nr. Dover, Kent, Eng.":"Hougham, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1244–after 1340":"1244–134